The paper deals with the problem of differentially private top-$k$ selection, which involves selecting a set of $k$ columns from a dataset. This problem is closely related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the composition properties of differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
